<HEADLINE> CKE Selling Off 350 Restaurants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- CKE Enterprises plans to sell at least  
350 Hardee's and Carl's Jr. restaurants over the next 12 months to 
raise money for its program to remodel Hardee's outlets. 
</P>
<P>
	The restaurant company also said Thursday that earnings  
second-quarter fell 54 percent as same store sales dropped for its 
fast-food chains. 
</P>
<P>
	The company earned $10.3 million, or 20 cents per share, for the  
quarter ending Aug. 10. That compares with earnings of $22.6 
million, or 42 cents per share, a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Revenues dropped 2 percent to $9.6 million for the quarter.  
</P>
<P>
	Overall same-store sales fell 3.8 percent, although same-store  
sales for 114 Taco Bueno outlets, which operate in Texas and 
Oklahoma, were up 7.8 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	For the first six months of the year, CKE reported earnings of  
$29.7 million, or 56 cents per share, down from $45.3 million, or 
88 cents per share. 
</P>
<P>
	Through its subsidiaries, franchisees and licensees, CKE  
operates more than 3,800 fast-food restaurants. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of CKE fell 18 3/4 cents to $8.31 1/4 in trading on the New  
York Stock Exchange. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
