<HEADLINE> Silverbulletday Returns to Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Silverbulletday returns to Belmont Park, the  
site of her only defeat this year, but this time she will be 
competing against 3-year-old fillies, not males. 
</P>
<P>
	And she is the early 1-5 favorite to beat them, as she almost  
always does, in the 1 1/8-mile Gazelle Saturday in her first start 
since finishing seventh in the 1 1/2-mile Belmont Stakes June 5 after 
having set the pace for than a mile. 
</P>
<P>
	In another Grade I stakes on the card, Honor Glide, winner of  
the Bowling Green and Sword Dancer handicaps in his last two 
starts, is the 9-5 choice to beat seven rivals in the 1 3/8-mile Man 
o'War on the grass. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday, ridden by Jerry Bailey, will leave from the  
rail in the six-horse Gazelle as she bids for her third straight 
win since the Belmont, her only race against males, and her eighth 
victory in nine starts this year. Her only other loss in 15 career 
starts was a fourth in the Del Mar Debutante last year. 
</P>
<P>
	In her last start, Silverbulletday won the 1 1/4-mile Alabama by  
nine lengths Aug. 21 at Saratoga. Her next start was expected to be 
in the Spinster at Keeneland. Trainer Bob Baffert, however, said 
Wednesday he decided to keep her in New York, where she also is 
supposed to run in the Beldame Oct. 9 at Belmont before going to 
Gulfstream Park for the Breeders' Cup Distaff Nov. 6. 
</P>
<P>
	She would face older fillies in the 1 1/8-mile Beldame.  
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday will carry 124 pounds and spot from nine to 12  
pounds to Country Hideaway, Gold From the West, Awful Smart, 
Queen's Word and Singing Rockette. 
</P>
<P>
	Honor Glide, ridden by Jose Santos, moved up in the turf  
division by winning the 1 3/8-mile Bowling Green July 10 at Belmont 
and the 1 1/2-mile Sword Dancer Aug. 14 at Saratoga. Division leader 
Yagli finished last in the Sword Dancer. 
</P>
<P>
	Others in the $500,000 Man o'War are Val's Prince, Fahris,  
Single Empire, Mash One, Federal Trial and Beautiful Dancer. Each 
starter will carry 126 pounds. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
