<HEADLINE> Canseco Returns to Devil Rays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Tampa Bay Devil Rays designated  
hitter Jose Canseco was back in the starting lineup Thursday night 
after missing four games because of an injured right hand. 
</P>
<P>
	``Jose looks like he's swinging the bat well and the hand is not  
bothering him,'' Tampa Bay manager Larry Rothschild said before 
Thursday's game with the Detroit Tigers. ``He's back in the lineup 
and a welcome addition, I might add.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Canseco hurt his hand during batting practice last month after  
undergoing back surgery in July. He went 12-for-37 (.324) with nine 
