<DOCNO> APW19990909.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 16:00:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Armed Man Menaces Abortion Doctors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) -- A man arrived at a hospital with a  
shotgun Thursday, saying he wanted to kill abortion-performing 
doctors. He was overpowered by guards and arrested. 
</P>
<P>
	No shots were fired and no one was injured in the arrest of the  
28-year-old Lincoln Park man. The suspect, who police did not 
identify, was in custody and was to be charged with assault with 
intent to commit murder, Dearborn police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The man drove up to Oakwood Hospital's main entrance about 10:30  
a.m. with a 12-gauge shotgun and was ``threatening to kill all 
doctors performing abortions,'' police said. 
</P>
<P>
	He told detectives that doctors who perform abortions are  
``murderers who must be killed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``The suspect further claims that a girlfriend or former wife  
had an abortion sometime in the past and he is avenging the 
so-called `murder' of his daughter,'' a police statement said. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators said the suspect was taking drugs for depression  
and was to undergo a mental examination. Oakwood spokeswoman Laurie 
Armstrong said it was not hospital policy to perform abortions. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
