<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Miss Suspends Two Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HATTIESBURG, Miss. (AP) -- Southern Mississippi receiver Sherrod  
Gideon and defensive back Leo Barnes have been suspended for 
Saturday's game against Northwestern Louisiana. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Jeff Bower said Thursday that Gideon and Barnes were  
suspended for violating a team rule. The coach didn't elaborate. 
</P>
<P>
	Gideon, the school's career receiving leader, caught four passes  
for 52 yards and a touchdown in Southern Mississippi's 
season-opening 48-14 victory over Tulane on Monday. Barnes had 
three tackles and an interception in the opener. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
