<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Over 10,000 Stepladders Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 10,700 stepladders are being recalled  
because of faulty steps that can cause people to fall. 
</P>
<P>
	The Consumer Product Safety Commission said the RIDGID ladders,  
made by Louisville Ladder Group of Louisville, Ky., have steps that 
are too short and improperly attached to the ladder. 
</P>
<P>
	The company received report of one step falling off, but no  
injuries, the commission said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The ladders were sold at Home Depot stores from May until July  
for $119 to $223. They come in lengths of 6, 8 and 10 feet, with a 
red plastic top and gray railings and model numbers that start with 
R-3011. 
</P>
<P>
	Consumers should call 1-888-318-7911 to find out if the steps  
are properly attached. Home Depot will exchange the ladder or 
refund consumers for the cost. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
