<HEADLINE> Rosie O'Donnell Selling Mansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NYACK, N.Y. (AP) -- Now that she's invested $290,000 on  
renovations, talk-show host Rosie O'Donnell is looking to move from 
the mansion known as ``Pretty Penny.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Her publicist, Jennifer Glaisek, said Thursday that Ms.  
O'Donnell is looking for more privacy and security than the 22-room 
home can provide. The 150-year-old house is on a main road in this 
New York City suburb. 
</P>
<P>
	The previous occupants, actress Helen Hayes and her husband,  
Charles MacArthur, bought the house in 1931. Miss Hayes said its 
name came from remark of a friend: ``This place must have cost a 
pretty penny.'' 
</P>
<P>
	O'Donnell bought the house for $770,000 in 1996. The new listing  
price? $2.75 million. 
  	   	
</P>
