<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 21:50:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clippers Buy Out Guard's Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Los Angeles Clippers bought out the  
remaining year of guard Pooh Richardson's contract on Thursday, the 
team said. 
</P>
<P>
	Terms of the buyout weren't disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Richardson, 33, has spent the last five years with the Clippers.  
He entered the league in 1989 as the 10th overall pick of the 
Minnesota Timberwolves. After a three-year stint in Minnesota, 
Richardson played for the Indiana Pacers for two seasons. He was 
acquired by the Clippers in a 1994 trade. 
</P>
<P>
	Richardson has career averages of 11.1 points and 6.5 assists  
per game in 639 games. He was hampered by an ankle injury last 
season and expressed frustration playing for the woeful Clippers. 
</P>
<P>
	Richardson played at UCLA.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
