<HEADLINE> Braves Acquire Garcia From Pirates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Third baseman Freddy Garcia was acquired by the  
Atlanta Braves from the Pittsburgh Pirates on Thursday for for 
minor league pitcher Greg Dukeman. 
</P>
<P>
	Garcia, 27, hit .231 with five doubles, six homers and 23 RBIs  
in 55 games with the Pirates this season before he was sent to 
Triple-A Nashville. He will join the Braves in time for their game 
at San Francisco on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Dukeman, selected by the Braves in the 1997 amateur draft, was  
0-1 with a 3.38 ERA in 17 games this year with Danville, a rookie 
league team. 
</P>
<P>
	To make room for Garcia on their roster, the Braves transferred  
pitcher Rudy Seanez from the 15-day disabled list to the 60-day 
list. 
</P>
<P>
	Braves infielder Marty Malloy, who had been designated for  
assignment, cleared waivers and was sent outright to Triple-A 
Richmond. 
