<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Plane's Landing Gear Breaks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Part of the landing gear on a DC-9  
carrying 46 people collapsed as the plane touched down Thursday at 
the Nashville airport, but the pilot safely steered it to a stop 
with the left wing dragging on the runway. No injuries were 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
	TWA Flight 600 from St. Louis was making a landing around noon  
when the left rear gear crumpled, airline spokesman Jim Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown said it was unclear what caused the accident. TWA  
mechanics were sent to examine the plane. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
