<HEADLINE> Fomer Governor To Celebrate 100th </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Former Gov. Jimmie Davis, who wrote the  
tune ``You Are My Sunshine,'' will celebrate his 100th birthday 
with plenty of green for a church close to his heart. 
</P>
<P>
	At least 900 people have bought $100 tickets to a benefit for  
the Jimmie Davis Tabernacle, a church in Davis' hometown that was 
built to celebrate God through music. 
</P>
<P>
	The church got about $25,000 from Davis' 95th birthday  
celebration and $20,000 from his 90th, said Davis' accountant. 
</P>
<P>
	At Friday's party, guests will get a steak dinner and will be  
entertained by gospel tunes. They'll also get a CD with 20 versions 
of Davis' trademark song. 
</P>
<P>
	And then everyone can go home early, because the former  
segregationist governor ``was really adamant about ending at 9 
o'clock,'' said Mary Lastrapes, an assistant to a state lawmaker 
who helped organize the event. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
