<HEADLINE> Missing Alzheimer's Patient Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- An Alzheimer's disease patient was found  
in a storage room at the nursing home where he lived, four days 
after his disappearance triggered a search by police and vigils by 
relatives. 
</P>
<P>
	Ward Baker, 81, was dehydrated and suffering from bedsores when  
he was found Wednesday. He was transported from Sherwood Place 
nursing home to a hospital where he was in fair condition Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with the nursing home insisted they performed a  
thorough search for Baker, who has difficulty walking and is 
generally confined to a wheelchair. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's been a tremendous shock, very traumatic,'' Baker's wife,  
Eleanore, said. ``He doesn't seem to know where he was or what 
happened to him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	While police continued investigating the disappearance, Ms.  
Baker said her husband wouldn't be taken back to Sherwood Place. 
  	   	
</P>
