<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Emmy Looks to This Writer for Wit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Bruce Vilanch is the man of a million punch  
lines, the wisenheimer of the Emmys and Oscars, the gag writer who 
delivers wit on demand like a Pez dispenser. 
</P>
<P>
	A writer on this weekend's Emmy broadcast, Vilanch has had a  
hand in crafting memorably funny moments on countless awards and 
variety shows. 
</P>
<P>
	He is the guy who gave Billy Crystal this line during the  
Oscars: ``A billion people are watching us tonight, except Linda 
Tripp, who's taping it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	When Whoopi Goldberg said this about Los Angeles -- ``L.A. If you  
can't be a star, at least you can be a star witness'' -- that was 
Vilanch's line. 
</P>
<P>
	He supplied Roseanne with this wisecrack on true-to-life Barbie  
dolls: ``I'm waiting for Trailer Court Barbie and Eating Disorder 
Barbie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Vilanch and Crystal also created the musical number for a Oscar  
broadcast in which Crystal sang: ``Those eyes, those thighs, 
surprise! It's `The Crying Game.''' 
</P>
<P>
	Lately, Vilanch has gotten screen time as a regular on  
``Hollywood Squares,'' for which he is head writer. 
</P>
<P>
	Next week comes ``Get Bruce!'', a documentary about Vilanch's  
role as hired hip man for the stars. The film opens Sept. 17 in Los 
Angeles, New York City, Chicago and San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	The movie follows his career as an entertainment reporter for  
the Chicago Tribune in the early 1970s, a humorist for TV programs 
such as ``The Brady Bunch Variety Hour'' in the late '70s and 
writer for almost every awards show in the business. 
</P>
<P>
	His credits include the Grammys, the Tonys, the Daytime Emmys  
and the People's Choice, American Comedy and World Music awards. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm down to the American Bulimia Awards,'' Vilanch, a tubby  
figure with shaggy blond hair and beard, said in an interview. 
``There's nothing else left.'' 
</P>
<P>
	For Sunday's Emmys, he is writing for hosts David Hyde Pierce  
and Jenna Elfman and preparing lines for nominees who want 
something funny to say in case they win. 
</P>
<P>
	When the idea for the documentary arose, ``I was kind of  
amazed,'' Vilanch said. ``How many people get a documentary made 
about them? It's me, and Hitler and Gandhi and R. Crumb.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Get Bruce!'' showcases his work preparing Crystal and Ms.  
Goldberg to emcee the Oscars, including material that wound up on 
the cutting-room floor. 
</P>
<P>
	To spoof Oliver Stone's ``JFK,'' Vilanch and Crystal pondered a  
number to the ``Fiddler on the Roof'' tune ``Tradition'': ``A 
gunman on the knoll? Sounds crazy, I know. But Oliver Stone might 
say every one of us is a suspect.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The movie features stars Vilanch has worked with, including Lily  
Tomlin, Nathan Lane, Robin Williams, Raquel Welch and Steven 
Seagal. 
</P>
<P>
	``You give great mind,'' Williams tells Vilanch.  
</P>
<P>
	Lane says of Vilanch: ``He's given more great lines to  
celebrities than a Hollywood coke dealer.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
