<HEADLINE> Pool Picked in Dragging Death Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRYAN, Texas (AP) -- A pool of 48 potential jurors was selected  
Thursday for the second Jasper dragging death trial, and lawyers 
will try to cut the panel on Friday to 12 jurors and two 
alternatives. 
</P>
<P>
	That would set the stage for opening statements Monday in the  
capital murder trial of 32-year-old Lawrence Russell Brewer. 
</P>
<P>
	Brewer's trial will take place 150 miles west of the Jasper  
County road where authorities found body parts of James Byrd Jr., 
49, after he was beaten, chained to a pickup truck and dragged for 
nearly three miles. 
</P>
<P>
	Brewer, his prison buddy John William King and Shawn Allen Berry  
were charged with capital murder in Byrd's death, which happened 
outside the deep East Texas town of Jasper. Byrd's body was 
discovered on June 7, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Jasper County jurors convicted King and sentenced him to death  
last February. 
</P>
<P>
	Prosecutors have said they believe the three men killed Byrd as  
a publicity stunt to promote their own fledgling hate group and as 
an initiation rite of Berry into the group. 
</P>
<P>
	Berry is still to be tried.  
  	   	
</P>
