<HEADLINE> McCrary, Ravens Reach Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OWINGS MILLS, Md. (AP) -- Pro Bowl defensive end Michael McCrary  
reached an agreement in principle Thursday with the Baltimore 
Ravens on a five-year deal. 
</P>
<P>
	Other than the length of the pact, terms were not released by  
the team. 
</P>
<P>
	McCrary, who had 14 1/2 sacks for Baltimore last season, still had  
a year left on his contract, but his agent was instructed to reach 
a deal before Sunday's season opener. McCrary staged a two-day 
walkout late last month to protest the slow pace of the 
negotiations. 
</P>
<P>
	McCrary, 29, had been seeking a six- or seven-year deal  
averaging $7 million per season, including a $13 million signing 
bonus. The Ravens countered with a six-year contract averaging $6.5 
million, including a $11.5 million bonus. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
