<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-09 15:20:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Love May Be Able To Play at Ryder  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OAKVILLE, Ontario (AP) -- Doctors have advised Davis Love III not  
to play golf for two weeks because of a pinched nerve in his back, 
although his agent said Thursday he fully expects him to be able to 
play in the Ryder Cup. 
</P>
<P>
	Bob Estes, who finished 11th in the standings and would replace  
Love should he not be fit to play, is leaving nothing to chance. 
</P>
<P>
	Estes plans a trip to The Country Club on Monday after the  
Canadian Open because he has never seen the course and doesn't want 
to be at a disadvantage in a worst-case scenario. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully, Davis will be able to go,'' Estes said Thursday  
after a first-round 71 at Glen Abbey Golf Club. ``He's one of the 
best in the world, and our side needs him. But if he can't play, 
I'm next in line.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Estes missed by one stroke playing his way onto the team in the  
PGA Championship last month. He had bogeys on the two of the last 
three holes for a 69 and a tie for sixth. Ben Crenshaw spent his 
captain's picks on Tom Lehman (No. 12) and Steve Pate (No. 14). 
</P>
<P>
	Love was out of town Thursday and couldn't immediately be  
reached for comment. His agent at Pro's Inc., Vernon Spratley, said 
Love was advised that rest and therapy should be enough to take 
care of a pinched nerve that first surfaced during the Sprint 
International three weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
	``Nothing is a certainty,'' Vernon Spratley said. ``If he knows  
he can't go, he has told Crenshaw he would let him know. But I 
don't think that will be the case. I think he'll be all right.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Despite feeling pain in the NEC Invitational at Firestone two  
weeks ago, Love still tied for 10th. Spratley said the plan is for 
Love to start hitting balls next week, but he has withdrawn from 
Jim Furyk's charity tournament in Pennsylvania, the Excelon 
Invitational. 
</P>
<P>
	Spratley said Love is being replaced by Sergio Garcia.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
