<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McEnroe Is Captain of Davis Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- By winning seven Grand Slam championships, 77  
career singles titles and 77 career doubles crowns, John McEnroe 
had his share of tennis thrills. 
</P>
<P>
	Right up there, though, was his appointment Wednesday as captain  
of the U.S. Davis Cup team. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is one of the proudest moments of my life,'' McEnroe said  
after Judy Levering, president of the United States Tennis 
Association, named him to the post. 
</P>
<P>
	Then he turned to Levering.  
</P>
<P>
	``Apparently,'' McEnroe said, ``it took this wonderful lady here  
to show some guts finally, and I appreciate that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McEnroe, one of America's most successful Davis Cup players, has  
staged a long campaign to lead the Davis Cup effort. He has always 
been passionate about the international competition and hopes he 
can bring that same kind of enthusiasm to top players who often 
have been uninspired about the competition. 
</P>
<P>
	Pete Sampras and Andre Agassi, who came into the U.S. Open  
ranked 1-2 in the world, have passed on Davis Cup play in the past, 
but seemed enthused about McEnroe's appointment. 
</P>
<P>
	``It is something that John has wanted for a long time,''  
Sampras said. ``I know he will do a great job as captain.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Agassi was delighted.  
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's going to be the best captain yet, by far,'' he  
said. ``John will make a huge difference. Now all we have to do is 
get Pete on board and we're all good. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've still got the best players. Let's get it done.''  
</P>
<P>
	Certainly McEnroe endorses that approach.  
</P>
<P>
	He said he had not talked with Sampras and Agassi yet but would  
do so at the first opportunity. Both gave him their blessings in 
conversations with Levering, who had pledged to get input from the 
players before deciding ion the next captain. 
</P>
<P>
	McEnroe succeeds Tom Gullikson, who had been captain of the team  
for six years and remains as director of coaching of the USTA's 
Player Development Program. 
</P>
<P>
	``I talked to John yesterday and congratulated him on his  
appointment and offered him all my best wishes and support in his 
quest to bring the Davis Cup back to the USA,'' Gullikson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Gullikson took much of the blame for the United States Davis Cup  
loss to Australia in July when Sampras played only doubles. 
</P>
<P>
	McEnroe was asked how he would handle that sort of issue.  
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know the details of that,'' he said. ``I prefer not to  
look at the past at this time. That was obviously a position that 
was awkward in some ways. It's easy to be a backseat driver at this 
point. I prefer to look ahead.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Looking back isn't a bad idea for McEnroe, though. He played on  
12 Davis Cup teams, five of which won championships. He still holds 
six United States Davis Cup records and compiled an overall record 
of 59-10. 
</P>
<P>
	``He is perhaps the greatest Davis Cup player in the history of  
the sport,'' Levering said. ``I think he can be just as successful 
as captain and bring that same passion and energy he did as a 
player.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The draw for the 2000 Davis Cup competition will be conducted  
Oct. 7 in London. At that time the United States will learn its 
first-round opponent for competition Feb. 4-6. 
</P>
<P>
	McEnroe was unconcerned about what country his team will face.  
</P>
<P>
	``Bring them all on!'' he said.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
