<HEADLINE> Copter Crashes While Fighting Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BAKERSFIELD, Calif. (AP) -- A firefighting helicopter crashed  
Thursday while taking on water to battle a 3,000-acre arson fire, 
and the pilot managed to crawl out of the burning wreck. 
</P>
<P>
	The unidentified pilot, who was working for the Forest Service,  
was in fair condition at a hospital. 
</P>
<P>
