	HUGO, Okla. (AP) -- Doris Richard Miller, owner of Carson and  
Barnes 5-Ring Circus, died Wednesday between shows in McCook, Neb. 
He was 83. 
</P>
<P>
	Miller started the show 62 years ago and built it into one of  
the nation's largest tented circus. 
</P>
<P>
	He had been traveling with the Hugo-based circus to celebrate an  
elephant's first birthday. 

</P>
