<HEADLINE> Hasty Returns to Chiefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Kansas City cornerback James Hasty took  
Wednesday off to ponder retirement. On Thursday, he went back to 
work with the Chiefs. 
</P>
<P>
	Hasty said in a statement that his ``intentions were  
misconstrued.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 12-year veteran said he never intended for the matter to  
become public. 
</P>
<P>
	After practice Thursday, Hasty said nothing about his absence  
the day before, declining to answer questions. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Gunther Cunningham said he wasn't worried about Hasty's  
desire to play or how he would perform against the Bears on Sunday 
at Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
	``James Hasty and I have a tremendous understanding,''  
Cunningham said. ``I'll tell you one thing, I'm not concerned with 
him playing the corner.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Cunningham said Hasty would not be disciplined for his absence.  
</P>
<P>
	Hasty is in the second year of a four-year contract with the  
Chiefs. He is the lone returning starter at cornerback after Dale 
Carter signed with Denver in the offseason. 
  	   	
</P>
