<HEADLINE> U.S. Soldier Dies in Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HEIDELBERG, Germany (AP) -- A U.S. Army soldier was shot and  
killed Thursday during a training accident in northern Bavaria 
state, the military's headquarters in Heidelberg said. 
</P>
<P>
	A brief statement from U.S. Army Europe said ``the soldier  
received a gunshot wound while participating in a training 
exercise. 
</P>
<P>
	It said the accident occurred at Reese Range in Bamberg and that  
it was under investigation. ``There is no indication of foul 
play,'' the statement said. 
</P>
<P>
	The military was withholding the victim's identity until  
relatives could be notified. 
  	   	
